{"title": "Dilemmas of a Facebook user relying on it for news", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-04-05", "content": "Like many Generation X netizens, I\u2019m a regular user of Facebook, a social media app that allows us to stay connected with friends and friends of friends, gives us access to a range of community groups we\u2019d otherwise not even know about, and helps us stay updated with events around the world when friends share information.\nI also use Facebook to share my articles with my 3,000 over Facebook friends, most of whom I have never met personally. They are friends, or friends of friends, and readers of The Straits Times."}